Hello everyone! Let's go?

In the python we have a for primitive types:
INT, FLOAT, BOOL, STR
int(),float(),bool(),str()

n1 = int(input('Digite um número:'))
n2 = int(input('Digite outro número:'))
Soma = n1 + n2
print('A soma do dois números é:',Soma)

int () Is a one primitive type for the whole numbers!!! 
However, I always have to remember to put them in parentheses. (This part of the message was done with a translator.)

n1 = float(input('Digite um número:'))
n2 = float(input('Digite outro número:'))
Soma = n1 + n2
print('A soma do dois números é:',Soma)

float () Is a primitive type for a numbers with fractional values
